meta { title = Getting Started, description = Install Tiramisu Docs and create your first documentation page in minutes., order = 1, icon = rocket }

Tiramisu Docs is a documentation framework powered by link { url = https://svelte.dev, SvelteKit } and the Tiramisu markup language. Write your docs in code { .tiramisu } files and get a polished, modern documentation site.

h2 { Features }

list {
  bold { File-based routing } — drop code { .tiramisu } files in code { src/docs/ } and pages appear automatically,
  bold { Built-in search } — full-text search across all your documentation,
  bold { Syntax highlighting } — powered by Shiki with support for dozens of languages,
  bold { Dark mode } — automatic theme switching with light and dark variants,
  bold { Sections } — organize docs into multiple top-level sections with independent sidebars,
  bold { i18n } — built-in internationalization with locale switching and fallback,
  bold { SEO } — sitemap\, llms.txt\, and skill.md generation out of the box,
  bold { MCP server } — let AI assistants browse your docs via Model Context Protocol,
  bold { Custom components } — extend with your own Svelte components
}

h2 { How It Works }

You write documentation in Tiramisu markup — a simple, function-call-based syntax:

codeblock { language = tiramisu, """meta { title = Welcome, order = 1 }

This is a paragraph with bold { bold text } and code { inline code }.

codeblock { language = bash, "npm install my-lib" }""" }

The Vite plugin compiles code { .tiramisu } files into Svelte components at build time, generating sidebar navigation, search index, and page metadata automatically.

